
[1]detention

   DETENTION, n. [See Detain.]

   1. The act of detaining; a withholding from another his right; a
   keeping what belongs to another, and ought to be restored.

   2. Confinement; restraint; as detention in custody.

   3. Delay from necessity; a detaining; as the detention of the mail by
   bad roads.
